  "prompt": "What is the best chinese restaurant in Schaerbeek?",
  "response": "Schaerbeek, a vibrant municipality in Brussels, has a variety of Chinese restaurants to choose from. The \"best\" restaurant can be subjective and depends on personal preferences, but here are a few highly-rated options based on customer reviews and local reputation:\n\n1. **New Sichuan**  \n   Known for its authentic Sichuan cuisine, New Sichuan offers a wide range of flavorful and spicy dishes. It\u2019s a favorite among locals for its generous portions and friendly service.\n\n   Address: Rue de la Consolation 70, 1030 Schaerbeek  \n\n2. **Le Mandarin**  \n   Le Mandarin is a popular choice for classic Chinese dishes, including dim sum, Peking duck, and noodle dishes. The elegant setting makes it a great spot for a special occasion.\n\n   Address: Avenue Gustave Latinis 30, 1030 Schaerbeek  \n\n3. **Lotus Bleu**  \n   This restaurant is praised for its fresh ingredients and well-balanced flavors. It offers a mix of traditional Chinese dishes and some modern twists.\n\n   Address: Chauss\u00e9e de Haecht 192, 1030 Schaerbeek  \n\n4. **Dung Fu**  \n   A smaller, cozy spot, Dung Fu is known for its Cantonese-style dishes and affordable prices. It\u2019s a great option for a casual meal.\n\n   Address: Chauss\u00e9e de Haecht 21, 1030 Schaerbeek  \n\nFor the most up-to-date reviews and recommendations, consider checking platforms like TripAdvisor, Google Reviews, or local food blogs. Enjoy your meal!",
